1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,500
Account Manager: Hi Jordan, thanks for taking the time. How has the rollout been going for your team?

2
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:22,000
Jordan Park: Mostly good. We're seeing strong adoption in marketing and sales but engineering is stuck. They have specific integration needs we haven't covered yet.

3
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:31,500
Account Manager: That's good context. What's the engineering team's biggest blocker right now?

4
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:42,000
Jordan Park: They need the GitHub integration to work with our self-hosted instance. The cloud version works but we can't use it for compliance reasons.

5
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:55,000
Account Manager: Understood. I'll loop in our integrations team and schedule a technical call by next Tuesday. We've done self-hosted GitHub before so it should be doable.

6
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:08,500
Jordan Park: That would be great. Also, can you send me the pricing for adding another 20 seats? We want to expand to data engineering next quarter.

7
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:18,000
Account Manager: Yes, I'll send the pricing tomorrow morning. Will it be the same volume tier or a different one?

8
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:24,500
Jordan Park: Different - we'd cross into the 100-seat tier with this expansion.

9
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:32,000
Account Manager: Got it. I'll include both annual and monthly options. Anything else on your mind?

10
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Jordan Park: One question - are we still getting custom training for the engineering team as part of the contract?

11
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:50,000
Account Manager: Yes, that's included. Once we figure out the GitHub piece I'll schedule the training session.

12
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Jordan Park: Perfect. Thanks for everything.
